(Decision
    "Query is its own logic plane in signal-type schemas — not a name suffix repeated across sibling variants. When a contract has N read-side variants all suffixed with Query (RecentRepositoriesQuery, ChangedFileQuery, CommitMessageQuery, EventQuery, CatalogQuery), the schema is missing the Query parent — the repeated suffix is the symptom of an unrepresented schema layer. The correct shape: one Match variant whose payload is a Query enum, with each former *Query becoming an inner variant. Generalises: repeated category words across sibling names (Query, Command, Event, Listing, Selection) are diagnostic of missing parent types in the schema."
    "The psyche also named the possible next split: query -> recent -> repositories"
    "Recovering intent that the previous agent did not log. The psyche critiqued repository-ledger's *Query suffix pattern around reports /123 + /124; the agent wrote the analysis (/124) but did not log the underlying psyche intent. This record fills the gap, drawing the substance from /124's reconstruction. Manifestation target: skills/naming.md (new section on repeated-category-words) + skills/contract-repo.md (contract-specific form of the same rule)."
    Maximum
    2026-05-19T18:55:00Z)

(Clarification
  "Considering whether Signal core verbs may be the wrong layer: perhaps Assert/Mutate/Retract/Match/Subscribe/Validate are Sema/database operation verbs, while Signal contracts may extend with domain-local verbs such as Message or Query on sockets that implement them. This is not settled; it is a low-certainty design question to brainstorm."
  "Maybe I was thinking wrong all along. Trying to fit everything into the core verbs when we could actually just extend with more verbs. Where, you know, certain verbs only work obviously on the sockets that implement those contracts. And perhaps the signal core verbs are not really necessary or not that they're not necessary. Maybe they're a SEMA. Maybe they're the SEMA core verbs since they deal with the database. Maybe we were, maybe this is signal SEMA is what we were actually trying to point that out. Because the whole idea was that these verbs work with the SEMA engine."
  "Psyche is reconsidering the recent Signal-core/root-verb model after noticing that repository-ledger Query and persona Message may want to be contract-local operation roots rather than payloads under Match or Assert. Capture as consideration, not decision."
